          <article class="post-type-page" id="article">
            
          <div class="intro-text">

                      <h1 class="_title post-title">English for International Professionals</h1>
              
            
              
    
        
  </div>
        <div class="components">

  
    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="english-for-international-professionals" class="__title invisible">English for International Professionals</h2>
                    </div>

    <figure class="_image captioned-image image-right-half">
  <img src="https://tie.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/403/2019/03/DG16_04_28_027-1090x728.jpg" alt="Instructor talking to students">
  </figure>
  
  <h5>All courses are online for summer 2020.</h5>
<p>For summer 2020, the following classes will meet online. Classes will be synchronous: students log onto <a href="https://uic.blackboard.com/">UIC Blackboard</a> to join class at the scheduled course time.</p>
<p>Our English for International Professionals short-term language program helps intermediate to advanced non-native speakers of English improve their listening, speaking, reading, writing and English test preparation skills.</p>
<h3>These courses are:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Open to all. You do not need to be a UIC student.</li>
<li>Convenient. Study weekdays, evenings, weekend or online.</li>
<li>Focused on the skills that you need to improve.</li>
<li>Taught by experienced English instructors</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> The Tutorium can issue the I-20 for students in full-time versions of these short-term courses.</p>



  
</div>

  
</section>

    

    
      

<section class="component  ">

  
    <div class="component-accordion js-component-accordion">

    
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="course-descriptions-schedules-and-fees" class="__title visible">Course Descriptions, Schedules and Fees</h2>
                            <div class="__description">
                <p>Don’t see what you’re looking for? We can create custom on-campus courses, online courses or private instruction to fit your needs. <strong><a href="https://forms.uofi.uic.edu/sec/8403036">Contact us!</a></strong></p>

            </div>
            </div>

    <dl class="component-accordion__accordion"
        role="presentation">

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="1">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-1"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-1"
          type="button">
            Conversation Skills
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-1"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-1"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="course-info" class="__title invisible">Course Info</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve their speaking and listening skills in social, academic, and professional settings. You will learn strategies for effective communication as well as techniques for improving pronunciation. You will practice key vocabulary and American conversational expressions to help you feel more confident in social, academic and professional situations.</p>
<h3>By the end of this course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Successfully and appropriately engage in academic, professional, and casual conversations</li>
<li>Recognize the linguistic acts that occur in a variety of speaking situations, and be more comfortable participating in these types of interactions</li>
<li>Understand and begin to use the features of American English pronunciation for increased comprehension and to improve your speech clarity.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<p><strong>Tuesdays and Thursdays</strong><br />
12:30 p.m. – 3 p.m.<br />
5 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> May 19 &#8211; June 18</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: The Tues./Thurs. section requires a free placement interview to join.</p>
<p><a href="http://go.uic.edu/Assess">Request your online placement interview</a></p>
<p><strong>Saturdays</strong><br />
9 a.m. – 12 p.m.<br />
8 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> June 13 &#8211; Aug. 8 (no class 7/4)</li>
<li><strong>Fall:</strong> Sept. 19 &#8211; Nov. 7</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Course Fee</h4>
<p>$575<br />
Tuition includes all class materials.</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://appserv7.admin.uillinois.edu/FormBuilderSurvey/Survey/UIC_School_of_Continuing_Studies/English_for_International_Professionals/English_for_International_Professional_Series/Survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="2">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-2"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-2"
          type="button">
            Presentation Skills
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-2"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-2"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="course-info" class="__title invisible">Course Info</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve comprehension and delivery of academic and professional presentations. You will develop an effective public speaking style to deliver complex information in an organized, professional manner, applying standard pronunciation features appropriately. You will also increase your ability to follow advanced academic lectures and professional presentations.</p>
<h3>By the end of this course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Display confidence while speaking to a group and in impromptu speaking situations</li>
<li>Organize and deliver a brief academic or professional presentation</li>
<li>Communicate ideas clearly by applying concepts of American English pronunciation</li>
<li>Identify strengths and weaknesses in a speech</li>
<li>Demonstrate comprehension of advanced academic lectures and professional talks</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<p><strong>Mondays and Wednesdays</strong><br />
12:30 p.m. – 3 p.m.<br />
5 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer: </strong>May<strong> </strong>18 – June 17 (no class 5/25)</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: The Mon./Wed. section requires a free placement interview to join.</p>
<p><a href="http://go.uic.edu/Assess">Request your online placement interview</a></p>
<p><strong>Wednesdays</strong><br />
6 p.m. – 9 p.m.<br />
8 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> June 17 &#8211; Aug. 5</li>
<li><strong>Fall:</strong> Sept. 16 &#8211; Nov. 4</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Saturdays</strong><br />
9 a.m. &#8211; 12 p.m.<br />
8 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> June 13  Aug. 8 (no class 7/4)</li>
<li><strong>Fall:</strong> Sept. 19 &#8211; Nov. 7</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Course Fee</h4>
<p>$575<br />
Tuition includes all class materials.</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://appserv7.admin.uillinois.edu/FormBuilderSurvey/Survey/UIC_School_of_Continuing_Studies/English_for_International_Professionals/English_for_International_Professional_Series/Survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="3">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-3"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-3"
          type="button">
            Pronunciation
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-3"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-3"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="pronunciation" class="__title invisible">Pronunciation</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This course teaches pronunciation and speech modification techniques for non-native speakers of English. You will work one-on-one with an instructor to learn the keys to clear pronunciation: correct consonant and vowel sounds and American-style stress, rhythm, intonation, and pitch. To practice these elements, you will complete listening and recording assignments and receive personalized instructor feedback that identifies both where you need improvement and how to develop strategies for change.</p>
<h3>By the end of this course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Learn the pronunciation, intonation, and stress patterns of standard American English</li>
<li>Practice techniques and strategies to make your spoken English clearer and more effective</li>
<li>Build fluency and confidence in social and professional speaking situations.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<p>10 one-hour class sessions with a flexible schedule.<br />
(This is a private course. You and your instructor will select a convenient day and time. A shorter or longer course is possible. Please complete <a href="https://forms.uofi.uic.edu/sec/6839757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this form</a> to sign up.)</p>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Course Fee</h4>
<p>$850 for 10 hours of private instruction</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before you want your first tutoring session to begin.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://forms.uofi.uic.edu/sec/6839757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="4">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-4"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-4"
          type="button">
            Effective Professional Writing
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-4"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-4"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="effective-professional-writing" class="__title invisible">Effective Professional Writing</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve their ability to write more effective paragraphs and emails. You will learn to understand proper text organization and appropriately present arguments in writing in a clear, logical and organized manner. This course also helps you to understand and apply the rules of written English, and to find and correct your own grammar and punctuation errors in academic or professional writing tasks.</p>
<h3>By the end of this course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Produce register appropriate emails for various situations</li>
<li>Demonstrate understanding of text organization</li>
<li>Demonstrate the ability to write a highly effective, organized, unified, and well-developed persuasive paragraph</li>
<li>Demonstrate knowledge of your individual grammatical weaknesses and ways to address them.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<p><strong>Tuesdays and Thursdays</strong><br />
9 a.m. – 11:30 a.m.<br />
5 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> May 19 – June 18</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: The Tues./Thurs. section requires a free placement interview to join.</p>
<p><a href="http://go.uic.edu/Assess">Request your online placement interview</a></p>
<p><strong>Mondays</strong><br />
6 p.m. – 9 p.m.<br />
8 weeks</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Summer:</strong> June 15 &#8211; Aug. 3</li>
<li><strong>Fall:</strong> Sept. 14 &#8211; Nov. 2</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Course Fee</h4>
<p>$575<br />
Tuition includes all class materials.</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://appserv7.admin.uillinois.edu/FormBuilderSurvey/Survey/UIC_School_of_Continuing_Studies/English_for_International_Professionals/English_for_International_Professional_Series/Survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="5">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-5"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-5"
          type="button">
            Online Grammar for Clear Writing
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-5"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-5"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="course-info" class="__title invisible">Course Info</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the <a href="https://uic.blackboard.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Blackboard learning management system</a> to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from your instructor.</p>
<p>This course focuses on producing clear, error-free writing at the intermediate to advanced level. Your instructor will guide you through advanced grammar review, writing sample analysis, and development of effective self-editing techniques. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.</p>
<h3>By the end of the course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Identify weaknesses in your own and others’ writing</li>
<li>Make fewer errors in advanced grammatical structures</li>
<li>Use effective strategies for proofreading and editing your own work</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Spring Term A:</strong> Jan. 17 – Feb. 14</li>
<li><strong>Spring Term B:</strong> Feb. 28 – April 4</li>
<li><strong>Summer Term A:</strong> May 29 – July 3</li>
<li><strong>Summer Term B:</strong> July 10 – Aug. 14</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Course Fee</h4>
<p>$400<br />
Tuition includes all class materials.</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://appserv7.admin.uillinois.edu/FormBuilderSurvey/Survey/UIC_School_of_Continuing_Studies/English_for_International_Professionals/English_for_International_Professional_Series/Survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    <dt class="component-accordion__title"
          role="heading"
          aria-level="6">
        <button
          class="component-accordion__button js-toggle-acc"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="panel-sectionID-2-6"
          id="tab-sectionID-2-6"
          type="button">
            Online Developing Effective Writing
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-2-6"
          id="panel-sectionID-2-6"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="course-info" class="__title invisible">Course Info</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the <a href="https://uic.blackboard.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Blackboard learning management system</a> to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from the instructor.</p>
<p>This course focuses on how to produce concise, clear writing at the intermediate to advanced level.  You will learn techniques for starting a writing project, working with outlines, creating clear paragraphs, crafting introductions and conclusions, and adding concrete details. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.</p>
<h3>By the end of the course, you will be able to:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Improve both paragraph and document organization</li>
<li>Be more confident with starting, revising, and concluding your writing</li>
<li>Clearly communicate ideas in a professionally written document</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dates and Times</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Spring Term A:</strong> Jan. 17 – Feb. 14</li>
<li><strong>Spring Term B:</strong> Feb. 28 – April 4</li>
<li><strong>Summer Term A:</strong> May 29 – July 3</li>
<li><strong>Summer Term B:</strong> July 10 – Aug. 14</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tuition and Registration</h3>
<h4>Fee</h4>
<p>$400<br />
Tuition includes all class materials.</p>
<h4>Registration</h4>
<p>The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.</p>
<p>Ready to  enroll? <a href="https://appserv7.admin.uillinois.edu/FormBuilderSurvey/Survey/UIC_School_of_Continuing_Studies/English_for_International_Professionals/English_for_International_Professional_Series/Survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Complete our online registration form.</a></p>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    
    </dl>
  </div>

  
</section>

    

    
      

